International Conference for
Free and Open Source Software for Geospatial

Presented by:

Welcome!

OSGEO and the Boston Local Organizing Committee are proud to host the 2017 FOSS4G International Conference in August of 2017 and welcome you to Boston!

Venue

Located in the bustling Seaport District in the heart of the city, the Seaport World Trade Center overlooks Boston Harbor and is central to many attractions.

Program

The program committee has prepared a full and robust schedule of speakers, paper sessions, talks, and workshops the week of conference.

Workshops

Conference workshops will take place the two days prior to the main conference and will be held at Harvard University, across the river from Boston in Cambridge.

Social Events

There will be many networking opportunities and events, including the opening party at Harpoon Brewery and a conference gala at the New England Aquarium.

Featured Speakers

We are proud to welcome esteemed thought leaders and practitioners in the field to join us in Boston.

Paul Ramsay

Solutions Architect
CARTO

Holly St. Clair
